[1] Russia (Chelyabinsk)
Date: Wed 20 Nov 2013
Source: New Agency RIA-ru [In Russian, machine translation, abridged & edited - Mod.CP]
http://ria.ru/don/20131120/978304309.html


For the 1st time in many years there has been an outbreak of measles in the Chelyabinsk Region. The focus of the outbreak, which has spread throughout the Urals, was the city of Tomsk. The 1st cases of measles occurred in the Roma population. The local authorities immediately instituted measures to prevent spread of this dangerous viral disease. Hospitals and children's clinics received supplementary measles vaccination, and unvaccinated individuals received one dose of vaccine initially.

The senior physician of the Chelyabinsk Region organised immunisation of all medical workers, teachers, and school employees under the age of 35. According to officials, 58 cases of measles had been confirmed so far. In Chelyabinsk city, 2 cases of nosocomial infection have occurred in medical staff attending sick children. According to an official statement: "At this moment no cases of measles had been notified in the Satka district and there is no immediate cause for alarm."

All medical staff up to the age of 35 years have been vaccinated. There are 15 108 people aged between 18 and 35 years of age in the population. A total of 14 524 of this age group have received 2 doses of measles vaccine, consequently 96.1 per cent of the population are considered to be protected. There is concern, however, that some parents are not permitting their children to be vaccinated; probably about 31 children are in this category.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In the Chelyabinsk Region, as elsewhere, deficiencies in measles vaccination coverage are being attributed to the migrant Roma population. However, the numbers of measles cases are small in relation to the non-migrant populations of these regions.

The Chelyabinsk (Region) is a federal subject (an Oblast) of Russia in the Ural Mountains region, on the border of Europe and Asia. Its administrative center is the city of Chelyabinsk. Population: 3 476 217 (2010 Census). Maps showing the location of the Chelyabinsk Region can be accessed at http://russiatrek.org/chelyabinsk-oblast and http://healthmap.org/r/60ZE. - Mod.CP]

